					<description><![CDATA[<p>A Funding Round Built on User Trust Livid has raised $10 million to build an ad-free video hosting platform for creators and small businesses. The funding comes from the original</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/livid-raises-10m-to-build-an-ad-free-video-hosting-alternative/" data-wpel-link="internal">Livid Raises $10M to Build an Ad-Free Video Hosting Alternative</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>A Funding Round Built on User Trust</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Livid has raised $10 million to build an ad-free video hosting platform for creators and small businesses. The funding comes from the original team behind a major live-streaming service. They sold that platform after years of growth. They later watched prices rise and users struggle. They say that experience shaped their commitment to build a fairer alternative.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Livid says its mission is simple. Build tools that people love. Build services that protect user choice. Build a platform that does not lock content behind fees or forced upgrades. The team argues that many video platforms use ownership changes to justify price hikes. They say users often feel trapped because their videos are too valuable to abandon. Livid wants to break that cycle.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Creators have grown frustrated with rising subscription costs across many platforms. They want stable pricing and simple tools. That rising frustration has pushed new demand for alternatives. Livid says this funding will help fill that gap with a service designed around clarity and user control.</span></p>
<h2><b>A Platform Designed to Free Users From Lock-In</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company launched a new tool called L.O.V.E. It stands for Livid One-click Video Exporter. It bulk-exports entire Vimeo libraries. It keeps folders. It keeps metadata. It keeps sharing settings. It requires no manual downloads. It also requires no commitment to move to Livid afterward.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The team says this is a direct response to years of user lock-in across the video hosting industry. They believe data portability should never be a premium feature. They say creators deserve the freedom to move their own content on their own terms. The tool was built by former team members who once watched users lose control of their files when a platform changed hands.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company says the most common search question about bulk downloads reveals a clear issue. Users cannot export video libraries in one click. They have no built-in way to move years of content. Livid argues this is not a bug. It is part of the business model. They believe users should never feel held hostage by the service they pay for.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The team built L.O.V.E. to be a universal exit button. Even if creators move to another platform entirely, their folders and settings remain intact. Livid says the tool is not a sales funnel. It is a statement about user rights. It forms the foundation of their view that creators deserve simple, empowering tools.</span></p>
<h2><b>Pricing Built to End Punitive Models</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_199720" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199720" class="size-full wp-image-199720" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/an-empty-space-the-background-showcases-_b_13L02lSbObVQIQu96mxA_CErhfAB_RD-aAs-GYgh2gQ_cover.png" alt="A single, clear pricing plan with creators enjoying ad-free video playback and features." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-199720" class="wp-caption-text">Livid’s transparent $10/month Pro plan offers 2TB storage, ad-free playback, and full features without hidden fees, giving creators predictable costs and confidence to scale. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Livid Pro plan costs $10 per month. It includes 2TB of storage. It includes ad-free playback. It includes versioning and custom branding. It includes analytics and bulk controls. Every feature sits in one tier. No complex upgrade ladders. No charges that appear without warning.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Livid says it built this pricing structure in reaction to the complex models used by many platforms in the industry. Pricing changes often arrive with no clear benefit to users. Some subscribers pay more because they did not commit to annual billing. Others pay more because they uploaded too much content. Many face hidden thresholds that trigger surprise fees.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Livid says creators deserve stability. They deserve to know that their video libraries will not become <a href="https://www.empower.com/the-currency/money/financial-liability" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external">financial liabilities</a>. The company says its pricing is simple because creators should never pay extra just to access files they already own.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes that transparent pricing will build long-term loyalty. They say predictable costs give small businesses and independent creators confidence to scale their content without fear of penalties. They want customers to feel supported rather than restricted.</span></p>
<p>More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/jeito-capital-1-2b/" data-wpel-link="internal">Jeito Capital Raises $1.2B to Drive European Biopharma Growth</a></p>
<h2><b>Building an Escape Route for Creators</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Livid was built by people who saw the internal effects of platform consolidation. They say the pattern is easy to spot. A platform gets bought. A new leadership team arrives. Prices rise. Product changes slow. Entire departments vanish. Users receive fewer updates. They also face higher costs. They have little choice but to accept those changes because their libraries cannot be moved.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Livid positions itself as the answer to that pattern. It is built as the exit door that many creators never had. The team wants to give users a simple way to regain control of their content. They believe platforms should compete on value, not captivity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The founders say this funding round will help expand the product and bring in more engineering talent. They aim to improve the hosting experience with new tools built around clarity and user trust. They want to make Livid the friendliest option in the video hosting landscape. Their goal is to create a platform that treats creators with fairness, transparency and respect.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Many creators have expressed interest in alternative platforms. They want predictable pricing. They want fast support. They want companies that place users at the centre of product decisions. Livid believes it can meet that demand with tools designed to reduce friction and eliminate hidden constraints.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Livid says it was built for creators who feel locked in. It was built for teams that want simple pricing. It was built for businesses that want stable tools. The company wants to lead a shift in the video hosting world by proving that user rights and business growth can work together.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/livid-raises-10m-to-build-an-ad-free-video-hosting-alternative/" data-wpel-link="internal">Livid Raises $10M to Build an Ad-Free Video Hosting Alternative</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
